@karalabe you mentioned that you guys made changes to the mining processes for low difficulty networks. 
I'm having an issue where my contracts on my private network never get mined.
and then I get `Error: Contract transaction couldn't be found after 50 blocks undefined`

I'm using 
Geth
Version: 1.6.0-unstable
Git Commit: cc13d576f07fb6803e09fb42880591a67b8b0ef6

my genesis block has:

```
"difficulty": "0x400",
"gasLimit": "0x8000000",
```

and this is how am deploying the contract


```
var greeter = SampleContract.new(_greeting,{from:web3.eth.accounts[0], data: code, gas: 4000000}, function(e, contract){
    if(!e) {

        if(!contract.address) {
            console.log("Contract transaction send: TransactionHash: " + contract.transactionHash + " waiting to be mined...");

        } else {
            console.log("Contract mined! Address: " + contract.address);
            console.log(contract);
        }

    }else{
        console.log(e)
    }
})
```

any idea what's happening ? are you guys seeing this issue?
